File: Beachgoers are urgedÂ to only swim on beaches that have lifeguards. DURBAN - Lifesaving South Africa has condemned attacks on lifeguards, after a video emerged of the rescuers being beaten up by some beachgoers. The incident took place at Margate Beach, in KwaZulu-Natal. Some four holidaymakers are expected to appear in the Ramsgate Magistrate's court following the brawl.